ZCZC OE98
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 022300 UTC
A COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED OVER
SCOTLAND ON MONDAY EVENING AND FOR MUCH OF TUESDAY BUT
WILL DRIFT INTO THE N SEA LATER TUESDAY. A WEAK RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE WILL THEN BUILD FM THE S. ON WEDNESDAY THE
LOW CENTRE WILL DEEPEN AND MOV INTO SCANDINAVIA BUT A
SECOND AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL MOV FM S OF ICELAND TO
SCOTLAND BY MIDDAY THEN INTO THE N SEA BY THE END OF THE
DAY. PRESSURE WILL THEN SLWY BUILD TO THE W OF THE
BRITISH ISLES ON THURSDAY. WINDS WILL BE OCNL STRG IN
NERN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS ON MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY
THEN BECMG STRG W WITH OCCASIONAL GALES IN SHANNON AND
ROCKALL LATER. SIMILAR STRENGTH WINDS WILL PERSIST
THROUGH WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY MORNING WITH OCCASIONAL
GALES IN SHANNON AND ROCKALL BUT MOD TO OCNL STRG LATER
